{"type":"message","id":"fa5c0a2b","parentId":"ea958208","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:49:48.924Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oicopja7t8rb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094715\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n2. Key pending task: TIC Experiment - Implement Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on pulse logs\r\n3. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe \"NEXT ACTION\" is clearly defined: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files.\r\n\r\nI should look at what pulse logs exist and create a script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Implements invariant/variant classification\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and what format they're in. I'll need to create a TIC experiment implementation.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes, the most recent pulse is `pulse_2026-03-24 094616.md`. I should:\r\n1. First list what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier script that analyzes them\r\n3. Implement the invariant/variant detection\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step that advances the Phase 1 advancement goal about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment implementation. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that repeat across pulses) vs variant patterns (new each time)\r\n3. Attempts to predict the next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against the success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me write this as a concrete file edit.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement the classifier on existing pulse logs to measure invariant/variant accuracy against the >70% success criterion.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs, classifies invariant vs variant patterns, and measures prediction accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [int]$TrainSplit = 15,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Helper Functions ---\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    param([int]$Count)\r\n    Get-ChildItem -Path . -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" -File |\r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n        Select-Object -First $Count\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Parse-PulseContent {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    # Extract key patterns: headings, code blocks, key phrases\r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        \"headings\" = [regex]::Matches($content, '^#+\\s+.+$', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Multiline)\r\n        \"code_blocks\" = [regex]::Matches($content, '```[\\s\\S]*?```')\r\n        \"action_items\" = [regex]::Matches($content, '-\\s+\\[[\\s xX]\\]')\r\n        \"goals\" = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(goal|phase|active|completed)')\r\n        \"mutations\" = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(mutation|old_text|new_text)')\r\n        \"timestamps\" = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[T\\s]\\d{2}:\\d{2}')\r\n    }\r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-InvariantFeatures {\r\n    param([array]$AllPulsePatterns)\r\n    \r\n    $featureCounts = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pulse in $AllPulsePatterns) {\r\n        foreach ($category in $pulse.Keys) {\r\n            foreach ($match in $pulse[$category]) {\r\n                $key = \"$category`:$($match.Value)\"\r\n                if (-not $featureCounts.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n                    $featureCounts[$key] = 0\r\n                }\r\n                $featureCounts[$key]++\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Features appearing in >=70% of pulses = INVARIANTS\r\n    $threshold = [math]::Ceiling($PulseCount * 0.7)\r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($feat in $featureCounts.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n        if ($feat.Value -ge $threshold) {\r\n            $invariants += $feat.Key\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variants += $feat.Key\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariants = $invariants\r\n        Variants = $variants\r\n        Counts = $featureCounts\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction ClassifyPulse {\r\n    param($Pulse, $InvariantSet)\r\n    \r\n    $matches = 0\r\n    $total = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($category in $Pulse.Keys) {\r\n        foreach ($match in $Pulse[$category]) {\r\n            $total++\r\n            if ($InvariantSet -contains \"$category`:$($match.Value)\") {\r\n                $matches++\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $ratio = if ($total -gt 0) { $matches / $total } else { 0 }\r\n    return @{\r\n        Ratio = $ratio\r\n        IsInvariant = ($ratio -ge 0.5)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction PredictNextPulse {\r\n    param($TrainingPulsePatterns, $InvariantSet)\r\n    \r\n    # Predict: next pulse should contain invariants with ~same ratio\r\n    # Baseline prediction: \"will contain\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:47:52\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360188922}}
{"type":"message","id":"dcbde957","parentId":"fa5c0a2b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:50:06.542Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me also read the log file that was just created by the pulse run to see the latest state. But wait, the file I just read IS the most recent log file. Let me now look at the pulse_2026-03-24 094715.md more carefully to understand what happened.\n\nActually, looking at the exec output, the pulse ran successfully and produced output. The file I read (pulse_2026-03-24 094715.md) is the log from the previous pulse (09:47:15), but the exec ran at 09:49. Let me check if there's a newer log file. The exec said the file was pulse_2026-03-24 094715.md which was the newest when I ran Get-ChildItem. The pulse script itself started at 09:49, so the new log would be from 09:49.\n \nThe pulse run just completed now, so I need to find the log file it generated. Looking at the exec output, I can see the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is the focus—the idea that causal structure equals invariant structure—and the TIC experiment on the pulse logs is how they'll validate this against the success criteria.\n\nThe file I read appears to be an earlier pulse from 09:47:15, but the actual pulse run just happened at 09:49. I should check if a new log file was created from this latest execution, since the Get-ChildItem command I ran initially would have captured whichever file was newest at that moment. I need to check what the most recent log file actually contains now that the pulse has run.","thinkingSignature":"0c8e0996dd893d854cbd6e7e58a019a59bbba92becdc20659f76dcf5838cc22c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nho31shd4s4c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 | Get-Content -Raw","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M