{"type":"message","id":"e3c9174b","parentId":"dcbde957","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:50:07.320Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nho31shd4s4c_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending actions include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune ? empirically (start: ?=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe big recent insight is the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending section, there's:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSo the most impactful single action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. Let me check what logs exist and create the initial implementation.\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse log mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 094715.md`. Let me create the initial TIC experiment implementation.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that can analyze them for invariants vs variants\r\n3. Implement the experiment script\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete, specific action - implementing the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear path: causal structure IS invariant structure. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment needs implementation on the pulse logs to validate this hypothesis against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation: a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs, classifies content as invariant/variant, and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy. This directly advances Phase 1 by testing the core hypothesis that compression discovers causation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Setup\r\n```python\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nEXPERIMENT_RESULTS = Path(\"research/tic_results.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n_recent=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load the N most recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n_recent]\r\n    return [log.read_text() for log in logs]\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariant_features(pulse_text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract candidate invariant features from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    # File paths mentioned\r\n    files = set(re.findall(r'[\\w/._-]+\\.(md|ps1|txt|csv|json)', pulse_text))\r\n    # Key phrases that indicate stable knowledge\r\n    phrases = set(re.findall(r'\\b(Phase|COMPLETE|PENDING|Goal|Insight|Architecture)\\b', pulse_text))\r\n    # Numeric values that persist\r\n    numbers = re.findall(r'\\b(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}|\\d+\\.\\d+|\\d+%)\\b', pulse_text)\r\n    return {\"files\": files, \"phrases\": phrases, \"numbers\": numbers}\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(pulse_i, pulse_j, threshold=0.6):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as invariant if overlap > threshold.\"\"\"\r\n    feat_i = extract_invariant_features(pulse_i)\r\n    feat_j = extract_invariant_features(pulse_j)\r\n    \r\n    # File overlap\r\n    file_overlap = len(feat_i[\"files\"] & feat_j[\"files\"]) / max(len(feat_i[\"files\"]), 1)\r\n    # Phrase overlap (most reliable for causal structure)\r\n    phrase_overlap = len(feat_i[\"phrases\"] & feat_j[\"phrases\"]) / max(len(feat_i[\"phrases\"]), 1)\r\n    \r\n    return (file_overlap + phrase_overlap) / 2 > threshold\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict which invariants will persist in next pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    return extract_invariant_features(current_pulse)\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs(20)\r\n    if len(logs) < 3:\r\n        return \"Insufficient logs (need 3+)\"\r\n    \r\n    results = {\r\n        \"invariant_classifications\": [],\r\n        \"predictions\": [],\r\n        \"classification_accuracy\": 0,\r\n        \"prediction_accuracy\": 0\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Cross-validate: test invariant detection\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        is_invariant = classify_invariant(logs[i], logs[i+1])\r\n        results[\"invariant_classifications\"].append(is_invariant)\r\n    \r\n    # Count stable invariants (appear in multiple consecutive pulses)\r\n    stable_count = sum(results[\"invariant_classifications\"])\r\n    results[\"classification_accuracy\"] = stable_count / len(results[\"invariant_classifications\"])\r\n    \r\n    # Test prediction: given pulse i, predict pulse i+1 invariants\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        predicted = predict_next_pulse(None, logs[i])\r\n        actual = extract_invariant_features(logs[i+1])\r\n        \r\n        # Measure phrase prediction accuracy\r\n        phrase_pred = predicted[\"phrases\"]\r\n        phrase_actual = actual[\"phrases\"]\r\n        phrase_hits = len(phrase_pred & phrase_actual)\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:49:45"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":771,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending actions include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune ? empirically (start: ?=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe big recent insight is the \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending section, there's:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSo the most impactful single action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. Let me check what logs exist and create the initial implementation.\r\n\r\nThe most recent pulse log mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 094715.md`. Let me create the initial TIC experiment implementation.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that can analyze them for invariants vs variants\r\n3. Implement the experiment script\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete, specific action - implementing the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear path: causal structure IS invariant structure. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment needs implementation on the pulse logs to validate this hypothesis against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation: a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs, classifies content as invariant/variant, and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy. This directly advances Phase 1 by testing the core hypothesis that compression discovers causation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Setup\r\n```python\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nEXPERIMENT_RESULTS = Path(\"research/tic_results.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n_recent=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load the N most recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n_recent]\r\n    return [log.read_text() for log in logs]\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariant_features(pulse_text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract candidate invariant features from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    # File paths mentioned\r\n    files = set(re.findall(r'[\\w/._-]+\\.(md|ps1|txt|csv|json)', pulse_text))\r\n    # Key phrases that indicate stable knowledge\r\n    phrases = set(re.findall(r'\\b(Phase|COMPLETE|PENDING|Goal|Insight|Architecture)\\b', pulse_text))\r\n    # Numeric values that persist\r\n    numbers = re.findall(r'\\b(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}|\\d+\\.\\d+|\\d+%)\\b', pulse_text)\r\n    return {\"files\": files, \"phrases\": phrases, \"numbers\": numbers}\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(pulse_i, pulse_j, threshold=0.6):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as invariant if overlap > threshold.\"\"\"\r\n    feat_i = extract_invariant_features(pulse_i)\r\n    feat_j = extract_invariant_features(pulse_j)\r\n    \r\n    # File overlap\r\n    file_overlap = len(feat_i[\"files\"] & feat_j[\"files\"]) / max(len(feat_i[\"files\"]), 1)\r\n    # Phrase overlap (most reliable for causal structure)\r\n    phrase_overlap = len(feat_i[\"phrases\"] & feat_j[\"phrases\"]) / max(len(feat_i[\"phrases\"]), 1)\r\n    \r\n    return (file_overlap + phrase_overlap) / 2 > threshold\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict which invariants will persist in next pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    return extract_invariant_features(current_pulse)\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs(20)\r\n    if len(logs) < 3:\r\n        return \"Insufficient logs (need 3+)\"\r\n    \r\n    results = {\r\n        \"invariant_classifications\": [],\r\n        \"predictions\": [],\r\n        \"classification_accuracy\": 0,\r\n        \"prediction_accuracy\": 0\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Cross-validate: test invariant detection\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        is_invariant = classify_invariant(logs[i], logs[i+1])\r\n        results[\"invariant_classifications\"].append(is_invariant)\r\n    \r\n    # Count stable invariants (appear in multiple consecutive pulses)\r\n    stable_count = sum(results[\"invariant_classifications\"])\r\n    results[\"classification_accuracy\"] = stable_count / len(results[\"invariant_classifications\"])\r\n    \r\n    # Test prediction: given pulse i, predict pulse i+1 invariants\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        predicted = predict_next_pulse(None, logs[i])\r\n        actual = extract_invariant_features(logs[i+1])\r\n        \r\n        # Measure phrase prediction accuracy\r\n        phrase_pred = predicted[\"phrases\"]\r\n        phrase_actual = actual[\"phrases\"]\r\n        phrase_hits = len(phrase_pred & phrase_actual)\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:49:45","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"times